bio: My name is Jovee and I am from the Philippines. I am a graduate of Bachelor of Science in Secondary Education Major in English. I have been teaching English online and offline for more than three years now. I've handled Chinese and Filipino kids and adults too. I enjoy teaching kids that are beginners because I find it a blessing, especially when they have finally executed the word or the sound that you've been teaching them. In my previous years of teaching, I've learned and gathered some strategies and techniques  that can help me teach students of various levels. Guaranteed that I will be of great assistance in honing your communication skills. My goal is to touch the hearts of my students to love learning endlessly. Let us work together and make learning more fun!
education: Bachelor of Science in Secondary Education- Major in English
experience: ESL teacher and Call Center Representative
interests: I love gardening and reading story books to the kids.

name: Mary Jane Francia
bio: I am Mary Jane Francia; they call me Teacher Jane for short. I am from the Philippines. I've been teaching English for quite some time now. I can teach learners of different ages. I am a caring, loving, and understanding teacher. I am here to help you how to improve your speaking, listening, and writing skills in English. My style of teaching is fun and interactive class one-on-one. Teaching is my passion, and I am ready to meet and teach learners around the world, and you're welcome in my class. Let's make Learning English fun and exciting. See you!

interests: I like composing songs and poems, sightseeing,  going on adventures,  taking care of dogs, cooking, traveling, and most especially, l love teaching and teaching learners.

bio:
Hi there! My name is Glodith. I am a Math Teacher by profession and  also an Online English teacher
because I wanted to share my knowledge and skills not just in Math but also in English. I've been teaching English for almost 2 years. I have also obtained a 140-Hour TESOL and TEYL Certificate.  I've gained a lot of knowledge and skills through my experiences in teaching with different kinds of students and was able to handle them. I am friendly, patient, understanding and passionate in teaching my learners. I'd be willing to help you improve your English communications skills in a very simple and effective way. Let's apply what  you already and know and add something new each day. I'd love  to make our sessions fun and engaging.
education: Bachelor of Science in Mathematics in University of Mindanao, Philippines
experience: Online English Teacher,  Math Professor in a University in an offline classroom teaching, Online Math Tutor, Customer Service in a Travel Agency and Production Analyst in a Manufacturing Company.
profession: Math Teacher and Online English Teacher
interests: I love traveling, reading books, listening to music, playing sports and crafting.
